The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 22: Amid prospects of a good kharif output, finance minister P. Chidambaram has expressed hope that the ban on the export of non-basmati rice would be lifted soon. I know that we were forced to put temporary constraints on certain kinds of rice ... hopefully these restrictions can be removed as early as possible, he said after inaugurating the new facility of rice exporting firm Tilda Riceland here.                            
	 New York, Sept. 22: US crude oil futures rose as the financial rescue plan, a weaker dollar and trimmed output from Saudi Arabia helped extend oils rally. On the New York Mercantile Exchange, CLV8 was up $2.67 at $107.22 per barrel, trading to $107.80 from $103.35.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 22: The Company Law Board has reserved its judgement on a petition filed by Emami seeking stay over the annual general meeting of Zandu Pharmaceuticals for inducting new directors.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 22: Bajaj Hindusthan Sugar amp; Industries has acquired Uttar Pradesh-based Phenil Sugars and merged it with itself. Phenil Sugars has two plants in Basti and Walterganj in eastern UP, each with a capacity of about 6,000 tonnes crushed per day.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 22: The RBI will impose penalty on banks which fail to settle their accounts in time following the auction of government securities.                                                                                                                         
